@DATABASE "Default"
@NODE "MAIN" "Pick-Tag"
@TOC "CONTENTS"
         ******************  @{fg shine}Pick-Tag v2.5@{fg text}  *******************
         ********************** 4-9-96  ***********************
         ***********  Written by Andrew Westwood  *************




                 ** Opens on any named public screen **
           ** Random choice of taglines or scroll and click **
                        ** Free registration **
                 ** String gadget to write your own **
                 ** Ability to call a spell-checker **
                     ** Supports new-look menus **
            ** Fully configurable from within the program **
                       ** Full keyboard access **



@ENDNODE

@NODE "INTRO" "Introduction"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 I started in comms about 4 or 5 years ago with a 2400 baud modem, Term and
AmyBW to read/reply to messages. AmyBW had a great way to choose taglines...
just scroll and double click on the line you fancied, really simple. I then
moved up to pointing on a Fidonet BBS. This was much easier, but
unfortunately with the new software I was now using I had no control over
the taglines as I was getting a random selection each time.

 This was no good for me, so Pick-Tag was born. The early versions looked a
lot different to how it looks today, mainly because of all the ideas I've
received.

Thanks guys!

@ENDNODE


@NODE "INSTALL" "Installation"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 To install Pick-Tag on your system simply double click on the install icon.
Or to install manually, simply drag Pick-Tag, Pick-Tag.Guide and Taglines
to your Mail: assignment, and Libs/reqtools.library to your Libs: assignment.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "OPERATION" "Operation"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 When Pick-Tag is first run you will be presented with the @{"Settings window." LINK "SETTINGS"}
From here you can choose such things as what editor to use, which taglines
to display etc.

 From your mail program you call Pick-Tag which in turn will call your
editor and then display the taglines. I've not found @{b}any@{ub} mail programs
that @{b}don't@{ub} work with Pick-Tag, and I've tried a few.

 As stated above, Pick-Tag in normally called by your mail program. But it
can also be called from the CLI and WB. There is 1 available option when
calling Pick-Tag from the CLI, and that is with the argument of 'SETUP'.
This will directly open the @{"Settings window" LINK "SETTINGS"} and exit when the window is
closed. Calling from the WB will also directly open the @{"Settings window" LINK "SETTINGS"}
and exit when the window in closed.

@{b}Please note.@{ub} This version of Pick-Tag @{b}can not @{ub} read the config from
versions earlier than v2.3. Please delete them and start afresh.
Sorry about that.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "MAINWIN" "Main window"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 When in the Main window, you'll have five buttons along the bottom.

'@{b}Ok@{ub}' will add the selected tagline to the end of your message, and if you
have chosen a @{"Spell" LINK "SPELL"} or @{"After" LINK "AFTER"} command, these will be called as well.

'@{b}Cancel@{ub}' will quit the program without saving the tagline, and as above, if
you have chosen a @{"Spell" LINK "SPELL"} or @{"After" LINK "AFTER"} command, these will be called as well.

 The @{b}CloseWindow@{ub} gadget will quit the program, but will *NOT* call the
@{"Spell" LINK "SPELL"} or @{"After" LINK "AFTER"} commands.

'@{b}Pick Random@{ub}' will select a tagline at, surprise surprise, a random line :-).

'@{b}Find@{ub}' will give you a string gadget to enable you to enter a string to
search for.

'@{b}Find Next@{ub}' will find the next occurrence of the search string.


@ENDNODE


@NODE "SETTINGS" "Settings window"
@TOC "CONTENTS"
@NEXT "MAINTENANCE"
 These are the gadgets in the Settings window. From here you can choose the
following.


@{"Edit file                 " LINK "FILE"}                @{"Screen                   " LINK "SCREEN"}
@{"Editor                    " LINK "EDITOR"}
@{"Taglines                  " LINK "TAGLINES"}
@{"Spell                     " LINK "SPELL"}                @{"Add dots                 " LINK "DOTS"}
@{"After                     " LINK "AFTER"}                @{"Add CR                   " LINK "ADD_CR"}
@{"Add line                  " LINK "ADD_LINE"}                @{"Filter                   " LINK "FILTER"}
@{"User name                 " LINK "USER_NAME"}
@{"Key                       " LINK "KEY"}



 When you have finished with the Settings window, clicking '@{b}Ok@{ub}' will save
the config to disk.
@ENDNODE


@NODE "FILE" "Settings/Edit file"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 This is the file to be edited. Usually this will be left empty as Pick-Tag
will automatically find the file name. Only use this string if you know the
file name and your sure it doesn't change.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "EDITOR" "Settings/Editor"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 The editor Pick-Tag will call to edit your message. Normally the file name
will be added to the end of this string automatically, but you may specify
where in the line the file name will go by using '%s'.

i.e. If the file name is T:Spot.Temp

String                   Result
------                   -------

C:MyEd -option     --->  C:MyEd -option T:Spot.Temp
C:MyEd %s -option  --->  C:MyEd T:Spot.Temp -option
C:MyEd %s -STICKY  --->  C:MyEd T:Spot.Temp -STICKY


The default is 'C:Ed'

@ENDNODE


@NODE "TAGLINES" "Settings/Taglines"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 The tagline file Pick-Tag will load into the listview, one tagline per line.
Maximum of 160 characters per line.

 Taglines maybe split by placing a '\n' at the appropriate point. Lines starting
with ';' are for your information and are not loaded. Blank lines maybe
added by leaving them blank. Lines starting with a space are displayed but
are not selectable. The default is 'Mail:Taglines'

i.e.

This is a tagline.
This is another tagline.


That was two blank lines!
 This line will be loaded but not selectable.
;This line will never be loaded.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "SPELL" "Settings/Spell"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Name of spell-checker to use, i.e. 'AZSpell:AZSpell'. Pick-Tag will
automatically add the file name to the end of the string unless a '%s' is
used in which case the %s is replaced with file name.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "AFTER" "Settings/After"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Command to run before returning to your mail program. If using AZSpell
you can use this opportunity to call AZ_Check or a script of your own. The
file name maybe added to the string by using a '%s'.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Add_line" "Settings/Add line"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 This allows you to add any line to the end of the message. When using the
internet 2 dashes '--' will produce a nice separator line.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "USER_NAME" "Settings/User name"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Put your real name here. It will be needed when you register.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "KEY" "Settings/Key"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 When you register I will give you a key number, put this key number here.
This will stop the requesters appearing when starting Pick-Tag.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Screen" "Settings/Screen"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Name of public screen to be made default. All windows that would normally
open on the Workbench screen (including Pick-Tag or Ed) will use this
specified screen instead.

 Also see @{"Special notes on Cygnus Ed" LINK "CYGED"} and @{"Special notes on Gold Ed." LINK "GED"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DOTS" "Settings/Add dots"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 If your tagline file already has dots at the start of each line, use this
so Pick-Tag will not add any dots of its own.

 Also see Maintenance/@{"Start" LINK "START"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Add_CR" "Settings/Add CR"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 This will add blank lines around the tagline.
@ENDNODE



@NODE "Filter" "Settings/Filter"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 If the lines in your tagline file are separated by special indicator lines
e.g. "%%" use this to filter them out.

 Also see Maintenance/@{"Start" LINK "START"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "MAINTENANCE" "Settings/Maintenance"
@TOC "CONTENTS"
@NEXT "CYGED"

 This window will sort out the "dead wood" from your taglines.

 Top centre is the tagline counter. To the right of this is the
@{"Additional tag requester " LINK "ADD_TAG_REQ"}

 The others gadgets are:

@{"Sort                     " LINK "SORT"}
@{"Edit tags                " LINK "EDIT_TAGS}
@{"Start                    " LINK "START"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ADD_TAG_REQ" "Maintenance/Additional tag requester"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 This will add taglines to your tagline file.@{b} DO NOT@{ub} confuse this
with the Settings/Taglines gadget, and @{b} DO NOT @{ub} select the tagline file
already chosen with the Settings/Taglines gadget.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SORT" "Maintenance/Sort"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Check this box if you wish your taglines to be sorted alphabetically when
@{"Start" LINK "START"} is clicked.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "EDIT_TAGS" "Maintenance/Edit tags"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 This will call the editor configured in the Settings window to edit your
taglines.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "START" "Maintenance/Start"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 This is the grand master of the Maintenance window. When clicked this will
dupe check, remove any dots from the start of each line remove any '%%'
separator lines and if the @{"Sort" LINK "SORT"} box is checked, will sort into
alphabetical order as well.

 Note. If you have comment lines in your taglines file these will be placed
at the top and be of no use.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "CYGED" "Special notes on Cygnus Ed"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 I don't use Cygnus Ed myself, but apparently there's a problem with Cygnus
Ed opening two screens when called by Pick-Tag. The answer is to set Pick-Tag
using Settings/@{"Screen" LINK "SCREEN"}, to open all windows on the Workbench screen.

Also, Cygnus Ed @{b}must not@{ub} detach after opening its window. Use the -STICKY
option to prevent this. See Settings/@{"Editor" LINK "EDITOR"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "GED" "Special notes on Gold Ed"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Here's another editor I don't use. Same problems as Cygnus Ed.
See @{"Special notes on Cygnus Ed." LINK "CYGED"}

Also, Gold Ed @{b}must not@{ub} detach after opening its window. Use
the -STICKY option or Y option to prevent this. See Settings/@{"Editor" LINK "EDITOR"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "AUTHOR" "Author"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 I may be contacted at by email at 'westwood@foobar.co.uk' or Fidonet
'2:2503/201.14'

@ENDNODE

@NODE "REGISTRATION" "Registration"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 @{"b"}Registration is free!@{"ub"}

 If you wish to register, just send me a quick message making sure that your
name is clearly displayed. I'll then send you a key number which is made-up
from your details and is personal to you which will unlock Pick-Tag and stop
the requesters appearing.

If you haven't received any reply from me within 7 days internet or 20 days
fidonet then re-send message.


Send your applications to:

 Internet-:     westwood@foobar.co.uk

or

 Fidonet-:      2:2503/201.14


If you would like new versions of Pick-Tag to be sent direct to you when
they are released please mention this as well.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUGS" "Bugs"
@TOC "CONTENTS"

 Bugs! What bugs? ;-)

 Pick-Tag has been tested on A600
                             A1200
                             A1200/30
                             A4000/40

 Please remember, that if you find a bug or Pick-Tag refuses to work with
your system. Don't keep it to yourself. Mail me explaining the problem and
I'll do my best to fix it.

@ENDNODE




